SIMPLE: propose
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Propose
<hw>Pro*pose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Proposed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Proposing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>proposer</ets>; pref. <ets>pro-</ets> (L. <ets>pro</ets> for,
forward) + <ets>poser</ets> to place. See <er>Pose</er>,
<pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To set forth.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That being <qex>proposed</qex> brimfull of wine, one scarce could
lift it up.</q> <rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To offer for consideration, discussion, acceptance,
or adoption; <as>as, to <ex>propose</ex> terms of peace; to
<ex>propose</ex> a question for discussion; to <ex>propose</ex> an
alliance; to <ex>propose</ex> a person for office.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To set before one's self or others as a purpose
formed; hence, to purpose; to intend.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>propose</qex> to relate, in several volumes, the history of
the people of New England.</q> <rj><au>Palfrey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To propose to one's self</b></col>, <cd>to intend; to
design.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propose</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Propose
<hw>Pro*pose"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To speak; to
converse.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There shalt thou find my cousin Beatrice,⟦br⟧
<qex>Proposing</qex> with the prince and Claudio.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To form or declare a purpose or intention; to lay a
scheme; to design; <as>as, man <ex>proposes</ex>, but God
disposes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To offer one's self in marriage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Propose</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Propose
<hw>Pro*pose"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>propos</ets>, L.
<ets>propositum</ets>. See <er>Propound</er>, <er>Purpose</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Talk; discourse.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proposer</ent>⟦br⟧
